  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic V&V 40 credibility package for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. The primary validation result intentionally omits a comparedAgainst link (W-AR-05 trigger). A secondary validation result cites a cannulated-screw dataset as comparator — a condition that overlaps the COU on loading mode, specimen geometry, and acceptance thresholds but differs on the screw lumen geometry, which affects stress distribution near the root and yield force predictions. The validation narrative presents this comparator favourably without examining whether cannulated-screw failure mechanics transfer to the non-cannulated COU.",
