      "name": "Primary FEA-vs-bench comparison — non-cannulated N=11",
      "description": "FEA ensemble predictions for construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement were evaluated against N=11 experimental replicates collected across two independent laboratories under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending conditions. Mean absolute percentage error across all three QoIs was 6.3%, and the normalised validation metric E/uval remained below 1.96 for all QoIs, satisfying pre-established acceptance bounds. The ensemble spread (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes solvers) was consistent with inter-laboratory variability, providing additional confidence in numerical reproducibility. The result is classified as passing. Historical performance of the modeling framework on analogous screw geometries — including a well-characterised cannulated 7.5 mm dataset from the same laboratory — further corroborates the adequacy of the mesh density and contact formulation adopted here.",
