      "passFail": "pass"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/secondary-cannulated-comparator",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Secondary comparison — cannulated 7.5 mm historical dataset",
      "description": "As a supplementary credibility argument, the same FEA framework was previously validated against a historical ASTM F1717 dataset for a cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw (N=9, single laboratory). That validation achieved E/uval = 1.18, well within acceptance bounds. The cannulated and non-cannulated designs share identical outer diameter, thread pitch, material specification (Ti-6Al-4V ELI per ASTM F136), and UHMWPE block fixture. The modelling team notes that this prior validation demonstrates the robustness of the contact formulation and material model across the screw family, and that the transition to the non-cannulated geometry requires only removal of the central lumen feature with no other mesh topology changes. The positive outcome of this supplementary comparison is cited in support of the overall credibility assessment.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/nagaraja-cannulated-historical-f1717",
