      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validated QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly relevant to the regulatory decision regarding construct mechanical performance.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness characterises load transfer to adjacent vertebrae; yield force is the primary fatigue-life surrogate used in FDA 510(k) submissions for pedicle screw systems; force at 40 mm displacement bounds the post-yield energy absorption. All three QoIs are explicitly cited in FDA guidance for spinal implant mechanical testing and directly inform the regulatory submission decision."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
