      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation activities address the same loading mode, screw geometry, and QoIs as the COU, with any differences between validation and intended-use conditions explicitly assessed.",
      "rationale": "The primary validation activity directly replicates the COU loading mode (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending), screw geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm), and QoIs. The supplementary cannulated-screw historical comparison is cited as corroborating evidence for the modeling framework's general adequacy. The validation narrative notes that the cannulated dataset shares loading mode, outer diameter, material, and fixture, and concludes that the framework is transferable. The difference in lumen geometry — which eliminates the central bore stress concentration present in the cannulated design and shifts the yield force upward by a margin not quantified in this assessment — is not examined as a potential source of non-transferability. This omission constitutes the primary credibility gap in the relevance argument."
