    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level of 3 due to the single-rate, single-temperature test protocol; this gap is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 specifies a single standard rate and that the regulatory submission is limited to static performance claims. The primary validation result (E/uval = 1.41 for yield force, the most demanding QoI) satisfies the pre-established acceptance bound of 1.96. The supplementary cannulated-screw historical validation (E/uval = 1.18) is cited as additional corroborating evidence for framework robustness. Overall credibility is judged sufficient for a Medium model risk, Medium consequence COU at the Medium assurance level. The assessment team accepts the package.",
